n a "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"background thread"}]},{"type":"text","text":" by default instead of a the main"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"thread. This creates a race condition during app launch:"}]},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Main Thread:","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" Proceeds with the standard launch sequence, making the app’s UI active and visible.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Background Thread:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Runs this notification code. By the time it can switch back to the main"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"thread, the app is often already active."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This breaks the critical assumption that code for a “direct open” notification runs ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"before","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" the app is fully","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"interactive. This can lead to incorrect direct open counts.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Migration","level":3,"text":"Migration"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To fix this, you must migrate to the synchronous version of this method, which accepts and forwards a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"completionHandler"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This guarantees your code runs on the main thread at the correct point in the lifecycle, before the app becomes active."}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"center: The notification center that delivered the notification.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"response: The user’s response to the notification.","type":